<dl id="n53046c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n53" href="#n53046c">N53 (VI.B.46)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n53all.htm#n53046c"> 46(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Linnaeus / better - <font color="green">[names]</font> ~</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[When <mark>Linnaeus</mark> created a grammar and a logic for his nomenclature of plants, he either gave a <mark>better</mark> definition or invented <mark>new names</mark> for some thousand technical notions.]</font> <small> Fritz Mauthner, <a name="FMBK1" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#FMBK1"><cite title="source">Beitr&auml;ge zu einer Kritik der Sprache.</cite></a> 3 vols (1901-2) III 507</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: Turquoise ink. Carolus Linnaeus (Carl von Linn&eacute;), 1707-1778, was the celebrated Swiss botanist who devised the modern system of nomenclature for plant species. </mm> </dd></dl>
